.TH "gluebi_write" 9 "gluebi_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gluebi_write \- write operation of emulated MTD devices.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gluebi_write
.BI "(struct mtd_info *mtd "  ","
.BI "loff_t to "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "size_t *retlen "  ","
.BI "const u_char *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mtd" 12
MTD device description object
.IP "to" 12
absolute offset where to write
.IP "len" 12
how many bytes to write
.IP "retlen" 12
count of written bytes is returned here
.IP "buf" 12
buffer with data to write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns zero in case of success and a negative error code in
case of failure.
